[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = BoostedDarkMatter","category":"page"},{"location":"#BoostedDarkMatter","page":"Home","title":"BoostedDarkMatter","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for BoostedDarkMatter.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [BoostedDarkMatter]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Kinematics","page":"Home","title":"Kinematics","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics]","category":"page"},{"location":"#BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics","page":"Home","title":"BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics","text":"The Kinematics sub-module contains kinematics function for elastic two body scattering,\n\np_1 + p_2  p_3 + p_4\n\nThe convention is 1  3 and 2  4. Currently, the functions in this module are given for the laboratory frame where the particle 2 is at rest.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"#BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.T1_min-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.T1_min","text":"T1_min(T4, m1, m2)\n\nMinimal kinetic energy of particle 1 required to obtain a recoil energy of T4 for the stationary target 2 in elastic scattering,\n\nbeginaligned\n    T_1^min\n=\n    left(fracT_42 - m_2right)\n    left(1  sqrt1 + frac2T_4m_1frac(m_1+m_2)^2(2m_2-T_4)^2right)\n=\n    fracT_42 - m_2\n    +\n    sqrtleft(fracT_42 - m_2right)^2 + fracT_4(m_1+m_2)^22m_1\nendaligned\n\nIn the case of T_4  2m_2 and left(fracT_42 - m_2right)^2  fracT_4(m_1+m_2)^22m_1, we need to expand the square root to avoid precision loss, and the result is\n\nT_4^min  fracT_4(m_1+m_2)^22m_1(2m_2 - T_4)\n\nArguments\n\nT4: Recoil kinetic energy of the target particle 2.\nm1: Mass of the incident particle 1.\nm2: Mass of the target particle 2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.T1_min_nonrel-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.T1_min_nonrel","text":"T1_min_nonrel(T4, m1, m2)\n\nNon-relativistic version of T1_min,\n\n    T_1^min = fracm_1 m_2 T_44 μ_12^2 = frac(m_1 + m_2)^2 T_44m_1 m_2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.T4_max-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.T4_max","text":"T4_max(T1, m1, m2)\n\nMaximum recoil energy of the stationary target particle 2 in elastic scattering,\n\nT_4^max = frac2m_2 T_1 (T_1 + 2m_1)2m_2 T_1 + (m_1 + m_2)^2\n\nArguments\n\nT1: Kinetic energy of the incident particle 1.\nm1: Mass of the incident particle 1.\nm2: Mass of the target particle 2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.T4_max_nonrel-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.T4_max_nonrel","text":"T4_max_nonrel(T1, m1, m2)\n\nNon-relativistic version of T4_max,\n\nT_4^max = frac4 μ_12 T_1m_1 m_2 = frac4 m_1 m_2 T_1(m_1 + m_2)^2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.reduce_m-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"BoostedDarkMatter.Kinematics.reduce_m","text":"reduce_m(m1, m2)\n\nReduced mass μ_12 = fracm_1 m_2m_1 + m_2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Index","page":"Home","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"}]
